    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Is D.H. Out of Order? The designated hitter may be an endangered species.</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Vincent said he did not have a timetable for eliminating the designated hitter, but hoped the change would be made. With the influx of new owners in the American League, the matter may be brought up for discussion and vote at a league meeting, perhaps as early as December. If a majority of owners votes against the d.h., the matter would then be presented to the Players Association.</p>
        <p>Because elimination of the d.h. would be considered a change in working conditions, the players union would have to approve the change.</p>
        <p>SPORTS PEOPLE: BASEBALL</p>
      </block>
